\begin{explanation}
   I assume that $d(x_0, x_1) \le r$\\ 
   Let $x \in B(x_1, r_1)$ therefore $d(x_1, x) < r_1$ to show: $x \in B(x_0, r)$ (i.e $d(x_0, x) < r$?)\\
   The triangle inequality states:
   \begin{align*}
       d(x_0, x) &\le d(x_0, x_1) + d(x_1, x)\\
                 &< d(x_0, x_1) + r_1 \le r\\
                 &\implies x \in B(x_0, r)
   \end{align*}
\end{explanation}